Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}(diced). Pick @Basil{1/2%ounce}(leaves picked from stems) leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves. Peel and mince @Garlic{1%clove}(peeled and minced).

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with half the @Italian Seasoning{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%teaspoon} in a medium #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #baking sheet{}. Top with half the @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup} (save the rest for serving). Bake on top rack until chicken is cooked through and cheese has melted, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Once water is boiling, add @Spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Reserve empty #pot{} for step 5.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add tomato and remaining Italian Seasoning. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon} and @Sugar{1/4%teaspoon}. Simmer until mixture is slightly thickened, ~{1%minute}. Remove from heat and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Stir in half the chopped basil and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Melt @Butter{2%tablespoon} in pot used for pasta over medium heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in drained spaghetti, 2 TBSP reserved pasta cooking water, and @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Stir in remaining chopped basil and season generously with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise if desired. Divide spaghetti between bowls and top with chicken. Spoon balsamic tomato over chicken. Sprinkle with remaining mozzarella and serve.

> "Margherita" isn't just for pizza, people! We've ditched the crust for juicy chicken covered in melty mozzarella with a warm balsamic-basil tomato topping, perched atop twirly garlic herb butter spaghetti.